<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1441,1053,1141]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1053,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In size and color, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[553,711,1053,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talaga">
<emphasis box="[553,711,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Beltia talaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[1002,1135,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="awapita">
<emphasis box="[1002,1135,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">B. awapita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the more rounded sides of the pronotum. The endophallus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[963,1074,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talaga">
<emphasis box="[963,1074,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">B. talaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also lacks the long sclerotized bar found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[349,483,1118,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="awapita">
<emphasis box="[349,483,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">B. awapita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
